{
  "stem": "422.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "He went to the cemetery and buried her.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And they were digging a very big grave, because that time could be-- were-- in the thousands, killed people in the Warsaw ghetto.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "So they were going to put everybody in one common grave.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But my father still had a couple hundred zlotys in his pocket.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And he bribed the gravedigger, and he-- he made a grave-- he should dig a grave separate for my sister.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "That's what he did.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Till now, I don't know where the grave is.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "No monument on it, nothing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "I don't know where she lays.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I know that she's some place on Gensia Street in the Warsaw cemetery, in the Jewish cemetery.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "This I know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Next day, mine-- my brother went out from the house also for some Jews.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And I watched from the street-- from the window, I saw another blockade.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And I said, who knows, to my mother, if my brother will come-- if he will come back.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And he didn't come back.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "He was caught.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And I don't even know where he is, where his ashes are.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "He was only 15 years.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "My sister was 18.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "He was 15.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A day after-- after the sister.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Can you imagine my mother's feeling?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Our feeling?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Losing one member of the family after the other-- after another one?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In 1941, the first victim was my youngest brother, who died practically from starvation from lack of medicine in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then was my sister.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "A day after was-- this was in July 1942-- was my brother.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "From all the three children, my parents remained only with me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then they said that everybody must work day or night, night shift and day shift.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So my-- my-- my father went to the small ghetto, they took him to work.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
